# DaisyUI + Angular CDK + Tailwind CSS

## UI Stack

- **Components**: DaisyUI v4 (semantic CSS classes, 55 components)
- **Behavior**: Angular CDK (overlays, a11y, drag-drop, virtual scroll)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v3.4.x utility classes
- **NO Angular Material** — never import `@angular/material/*`
- **NO Spartan UI** — never import `@spartan-ng/*`

> **Important**: Utilitzem Tailwind CSS v3 + DaisyUI v4. Veure `docs/TAILWIND_VERSION.md` per detalls.

## Theming

### Multi-Colla Theming with DaisyUI

DaisyUI provides built-in theme support via `data-theme` attribute:

```html
<html data-theme="colla-barcelona">
```

Custom themes defined in `tailwind.config.js`:

```javascript
daisyui: {
  themes: [
    {
      'colla-barcelona': {
        'primary': '#1B5E20',
        'secondary': '#FDD835',
        'accent': '#37cdbe',
        'neutral': '#3d4451',
        'base-100': '#ffffff',
      },
    },
    'light',
    // 'dark',
  ],
}
```

Future colles add new theme objects. Switch themes at runtime by changing `data-theme` attribute.

### CSS Variables (Legacy Support)

Keep existing CSS variables for Tailwind utility compatibility:

```scss
:root {
  --colla-primary: #1B5E20;
  --colla-secondary: #FDD835;
  --colla-text-on-primary: #FFFFFF;
}
```

Use via Tailwind: `bg-colla-primary`, `text-colla-secondary`

## Responsive Design

- **Mobile-first**: Base styles = mobile, `lg:` prefix = desktop
- **Breakpoints**: sm (640px), md (768px), lg (1024px), xl (1280px)
- **Touch targets**: min 44x44px on mobile (`min-h-[44px] min-w-[44px]`)
- **Tables**: Full table on ≥lg, card layout on <lg
- **Forms**: Single column <md, multi-column ≥md
- **Sidebar**: Hidden <lg (DaisyUI drawer), visible ≥lg

## DaisyUI Component Patterns

### Buttons

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
<button class="btn btn-outline">Outline</button>
<button class="btn btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
<button class="btn btn-sm">Small</button>
<button class="btn btn-lg">Large</button>
```

### Tables

```html
<div class="overflow-x-auto">
  <table class="table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Name</th>
        <th>Position</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Joan García</td>
        <td>Primeres</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```

Variants: `table-zebra`, `table-pin-rows`, `table-pin-cols`

### Forms

```html
<label class="form-control w-full max-w-xs">
  <div class="label">
    <span class="label-text">Nom</span>
  </div>
  <input type="text" class="input input-bordered w-full" />
</label>

<select class="select select-bordered w-full max-w-xs">
  <option disabled selected>Tria una posició</option>
  <option>Primeres</option>
  <option>Vents</option>
</select>
```

### Badges

```html
<div class="badge badge-primary">Primary</div>
<div class="badge badge-secondary">Secondary</div>
<div class="badge badge-outline">Outline</div>
```

Dynamic colors with inline styles:

```html
<div class="badge" [style.backgroundColor]="position.color">
  {{ position.name }}
</div>
```

### Drawer (Mobile Sidebar)

```html
<div class="drawer lg:drawer-open">
  <input id="main-drawer" type="checkbox" class="drawer-toggle" />
  <div class="drawer-content">
    <!-- Page content -->
    <label for="main-drawer" class="btn btn-ghost lg:hidden">
      <svg>...</svg>
    </label>
  </div>
  <div class="drawer-side">
    <label for="main-drawer" class="drawer-overlay"></label>
    <ul class="menu p-4 w-80 bg-base-200">
      <!-- Sidebar content -->
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Modal

```html
<dialog id="my-modal" class="modal">
  <div class="modal-box">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg">Modal Title</h3>
    <p class="py-4">Modal content</p>
    <div class="modal-action">
      <form method="dialog">
        <button class="btn">Tancar</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</dialog>

<!-- Open with -->
<button class="btn" onclick="my-modal.showModal()">Open</button>
```

### Progress

```html
<progress class="progress progress-primary w-56" value="70" max="100"></progress>
```

### Divider

```html
<div class="divider">OR</div>
```

### Toast / Alert

```html
<div class="toast toast-top toast-end">
  <div class="alert alert-info">
    <span>New message arrived.</span>
  </div>
</div>
```

## When to Use Angular CDK

DaisyUI handles styling. Use CDK for complex behavior:

### CDK Overlay

For programmatic modals, dropdowns, tooltips:

```typescript
import { Overlay, OverlayRef } from '@angular/cdk/overlay';
import { ComponentPortal } from '@angular/cdk/portal';

constructor(private overlay: Overlay) {}

openDialog() {
  const overlayRef = this.overlay.create({
    positionStrategy: this.overlay.position().global().centerHorizontally().centerVertically(),
    hasBackdrop: true,
  });
  const portal = new ComponentPortal(MyDialogComponent);
  overlayRef.attach(portal);
}
```

### CDK A11y (Accessibility)

```typescript
import { FocusTrap, FocusTrapFactory } from '@angular/cdk/a11y';

@ViewChild('dialogElement') dialogElement!: ElementRef;
private focusTrap!: FocusTrap;

constructor(private focusTrapFactory: FocusTrapFactory) {}

ngAfterViewInit() {
  this.focusTrap = this.focusTrapFactory.create(this.dialogElement.nativeElement);
  this.focusTrap.focusInitialElementWhenReady();
}
```

### CDK Drag & Drop (for Canvas/Figure Module)

```typescript
import { CdkDragDrop, moveItemInArray } from '@angular/cdk/drag-drop';

<div cdkDropList (cdkDropListDropped)="drop($event)">
  <div *ngFor="let item of items" cdkDrag>{{ item }}</div>
</div>

drop(event: CdkDragDrop<string[]>) {
  moveItemInArray(this.items, event.previousIndex, event.currentIndex);
}
```

## Component Structure

**IMPORTANT**: See `angular-component-structure.mdc` for mandatory three-file structure.

```typescript
// example.component.ts
import { Component, ChangeDetectionStrategy } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-example',
  standalone: true,
  changeDetection: ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush,
  imports: [CommonModule],
  templateUrl: './example.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./example.component.css'],
  host: { class: 'block' }, // Tailwind needs block display
})
export class ExampleComponent {}
```

```html
<!-- example.component.html -->
<button class="btn btn-primary">
  Click me
</button>
```

## Styling Rules

- All visual styling via DaisyUI semantic classes + Tailwind utilities
- No component-level SCSS except complex animations
- Use `@apply` sparingly (prefer inline utilities)
- Dynamic colors: `[style.backgroundColor]` binding or `bg-[var(--custom)]`
- Catalan UI text per `muixer-language.mdc`

## DaisyUI Components Available

55 components including:

- **Actions**: Button, Dropdown, Modal, Swap
- **Data Display**: Badge, Card, Table, Stat, Timeline
- **Data Input**: Checkbox, Input, Radio, Range, Select, Textarea, Toggle
- **Layout**: Divider, Drawer, Footer, Hero, Join, Stack
- **Navigation**: Breadcrumbs, Menu, Navbar, Pagination, Steps, Tabs
- **Feedback**: Alert, Loading, Progress, Toast, Tooltip

Full list: https://v4.daisyui.com/components
